{"id":"project-LICHEN-ks7t","title":"meshcore_error_from_errno default case includes -ENOTSUP","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Lines: 420-443 (meshcore_error_from_errno)

```c
static uint8_t meshcore_error_from_errno(int err)
{
    switch (err) {
    case -ENOENT:
    case -ENODEV:
    case -ENOTCONN:
        return LICHEN_MESHCORE_ERR_NOT_FOUND;
    // ... other cases ...
    case -ENOTSUP:
    case -ENOSYS:
    default:
        return LICHEN_MESHCORE_ERR_UNSUPPORTED_CMD;
    }
}
```

The default case includes -ENOTSUP and -ENOSYS explicitly, but they fall through to default anyway. While not a bug, this is misleading - it suggests -ENOTSUP and -ENOSYS need special handling, but they get the same result as any unknown error.

More concerning: positive errno values (if any callback mistakenly returns them without negation) would also map to UNSUPPORTED_CMD, potentially hiding bugs.

Consider either:
1. Remove -ENOTSUP/-ENOSYS from explicit cases (they match default)
